## Risk & Compliance

| Change | Business Risk | Regulatory Angle | Act By |
|---|---|---|---|
| **[ACR Stealer credential theft campaign](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/)** | Attackers are using fake on-screen prompts ("ClickFix" lures) to steal browser passwords and authentication tokens from enterprise users. Stolen credentials enable account takeover, data exfiltration, and lateral movement across your environment. | SOC 2, HIPAA, cyber insurance breach notification triggers, NIST CSF Detect/Respond | Immediate |
| **[Exchange Server 2016 and 2019 ESU program ends October 2026](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033)** | After October, these servers receive no further security patches. A known vulnerability discovered in November 2026 will remain permanently unpatched. Email is a high-value attack target. Running unpatched email infrastructure at scale is a material risk. | HIPAA (addressable safeguards for email containing PHI), CMMC (patching requirements), cyber insurance coverage conditions | October 31, 2026 |
| **[ShinyHunters OAuth abuse targeting SaaS applications](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/defending-saas-based-applications-against-shinyhunters-oauth-abuse/)** | An active threat actor is exploiting misconfigured guest access and OAuth app permissions in SaaS environments. Organizations with loosely governed third-party app integrations are at elevated risk of unauthorized access without triggering traditional login alerts. Closes an implicit-trust gap in federated identity chains. | SOC 2, NIST CSF Identify/Protect, GDPR (unauthorized access to personal data), state privacy laws | Within 30 days |
| **[July 2026 Exchange Server Security Updates](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/released-july-2026-exchange-server-security-updates/ba-p/4534146)** | Microsoft released patches for on-premises Exchange SE, 2019, and 2016 this month. Organizations enrolled in the ESU program must apply these patches promptly. Unpatched Exchange servers are among the most commonly exploited enterprise assets. | CMMC, HIPAA, SOC 2 patch management controls | Within 14 days |
| **[GigaWiper destructive backdoor analysis](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/09/gigawiper-anatomy-of-a-destructive-backdoor-assembled-from-multiple-malware/)** | GigaWiper combines data-wiping and ransomware-like capabilities into a single platform. Organizations without tested incident response and recovery playbooks face extended downtime if infected. Strengthens the case for reviewed backup and recovery procedures. | NIST CSF Recover, cyber insurance business interruption provisions, SOC 2 availability criteria | Within 30 days |
| **[Passkeys are now the default authentication method in Entra ID](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/)** | Microsoft is shifting passkeys to the default sign-in experience and changing how SMS and voice authentication work. Organizations that have not prepared their helpdesk and employee communications will see authentication confusion and support volume spikes. Replaces a weaker, phishable factor with a phishing-resistant one, a meaningful step in Zero Trust maturity. | NIST CSF Protect, CMMC phishing-resistant MFA requirements, cyber insurance MFA attestation | Within 30 days |
| **[Purview DLP for Copilot to restrict external email processing](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561552)** | Once available, this control will prevent Microsoft 365 Copilot and Copilot Chat from summarizing or reasoning over emails received from outside your organization. Organizations in regulated industries should plan to enable this at general availability to reduce AI-assisted data exposure. | HIPAA, GDPR, state privacy laws, SOC 2 data handling | Preview now; GA January 2027 |
| **[Entra PIM custom extensions enter preview](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/bring-business-logic-into-pim-role-activation-workflows/ba-p/4531380)** | Privileged role activation can now be gated on external business signals such as ticketing systems, HR status, or on-call schedules. Organizations relying on standing administrative access can use this to enforce just-in-time access with real business context, strengthening least-privilege enforcement at the privileged access tier. | CMMC, SOC 2, NIST CSF Protect | Evaluate in 60 days |
| **[AI agent identity governance now generally available](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-entra-blog/govern-ai-agent-identities-and-access-the-same-way-you-govern/ba-p/4529302)** | AI agents operating in your environment without formal identity governance are an uncontrolled access risk. This capability allows you to assign, scope, and audit agent access the same way you manage employee accounts. Extends verification to a previously unmanaged trust zone. | SOC 2, NIST CSF Govern, CMMC supply chain and access controls | Within 60 days |
| **[MCP security risks in production AI environments](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-security-community/the-state-of-mcp-security-in-2026/ba-p/4531327)** | The Model Context Protocol is now the standard way AI agents connect to tools and enterprise data. Microsoft's own analysis confirms that organizations moving agents to production without reviewing tool permissions, trust boundaries, and credential handling are accepting significant risk. | SOC 2, NIST CSF Govern/Protect, CMMC | Within 60 days |
| **[Post-quantum cryptography now in Windows 11](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-security-community/new-windows-features-to-secure-today-s-data-in-a-post-quantum-world/ba-p/4523370)** | Windows 11 now supports quantum-resistant encryption protocols for TLS connections. Data encrypted today with traditional methods may be vulnerable to future quantum decryption attacks. Organizations handling data with long confidentiality requirements should begin planning their transition. | NIST CSF, FedRAMP emerging cryptography guidance, CMMC | 12-month planning horizon |

*Sources: [Microsoft Security Blog – ACR Stealer](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/16/acr-stealer-two-observed-intrusion-chains-amid-increased-threat-activity/) · [Exchange Team Blog – ESU Reminder](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033) · [Microsoft Entra Blog – Passkeys Default](https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/blog/2026/07/13/microsoft-entra-id-security-updates-passkeys-are-the-default-authentication-method-in-entra-id/)*

