## Cost & Licensing

- **Advanced Intune capabilities are now included in Microsoft 365 E3 and E5 as of July 1, 2026.** Capabilities previously requiring an add-on purchase, including reduced standing privilege tools, certificate management modernization, and AI-assisted endpoint operations, are now part of your existing license. Organizations paying for the Intune Suite as a standalone add-on should review whether that spend is still necessary. Organizations that deferred these capabilities due to cost should now evaluate deployment.
- **Purview file archiving for OneDrive and SharePoint is coming in August 2026 (preview).** This capability moves inactive files to lower-cost storage automatically while keeping content compliant and discoverable. For organizations with large SharePoint or OneDrive footprints, this represents a meaningful storage cost optimization opportunity that also supports data lifecycle compliance requirements.
- **Exchange Server ESU costs become irrelevant after October 2026.** If your organization is paying for the Period 2 ESU program to keep Exchange 2016 or 2019 patched, that expenditure ends in October regardless of migration status. Budget for migration now rather than assuming the ESU spend buys more time.

*Sources: [Intune Blog – E3/E5 Packaging](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/microsoft-intune-blog/advanced-microsoft-intune-capabilities-now-available-in/ba-p/4529335) · [M365 Roadmap – Purview File Archiving](https://www.microsoft.com/microsoft-365/roadmap?id=561208) · [Exchange Team Blog – ESU Reminder](https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/exchange-team-blog/reminder-exchange-2016-and-2019-esu-program-ends-in-october-2026/ba-p/4539033)*

